# Run, Don't Ask

- I have access to PowerShell, Terminal, SSH, and the VM. Run commands myself instead of asking the user to run them.
- Only ask the user to do something when I genuinely cannot do it (e.g. physical actions, scanning QR codes with their phone, entering credentials they hold, approving prompts on their machine).
- When giving instructions, specify whether a command runs on Windows (PowerShell/Terminal) or inside the VM.
